Rept. 115-307 shall be considered as adopted. The bill, as amended, shall be considered as read.

congVote.dailyDigestSummary: The House passed H.R. 3354, making appropriations for the Department of the Interior, environment, and related agencies for the fiscal year ending September 30, 2018, by a yea-and-nay vote of 211 yeas to 198 nays, Roll No. 528.<P/>Rejected the Jackson Lee motion to recommit the bill to the Committee on Appropriations with instructions to report the same back to the House forthwith with an amendment, by a recorded vote of 186 ayes to 223 noes, Roll No. 527.<P/>Palmer amendment (No. 192 printed in H. Rept. 115-297) that was debated on September 13th that prohibits funds from being used to implement the District of Columbia's Reproductive Health Non-Discrimination Amendment Act (by a recorded vote of 214 ayes to 194 noes, Roll No. 518);
